 -- Corrected more typos in the aggregation docs. Thanks to Ivan Sagalaev for his eagle eyes.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:57','2009-05-16 00:46:57','russellm'),(6508,'9754','2009-01-15 23:15:32',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/db/aggregation.txt','Fixed #10039 -- More typos in aggregation docs. Seriously, people, now you\'re just making me look bad :-) Thanks to ElliottM, and to Erich Holscher for a separate report that I\'ve piggybacked on this checkin.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:57','2009-05-16 00:46:57','russellm'),(6509,'9755','2009-01-16 00:02:35',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/db/aggregation.txt','Fixed #10042 -- YAADT (Aggregation Docs Typo).',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','russellm'),(6510,'9756','2009-01-16 02:30:22',0,0,11,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AUTHORS\ndjango/db/backends/creation.py\ndjango/test/__init__.py\ndjango/test/client.py\ndjango/test/simple.py\ndjango/test/testcases.py\ndocs/topics/testing.txt\ntests/regressiontests/comment_tests/tests/comment_view_tests.py\ntests/regressiontests/comment_tests/tests/moderation_view_tests.py\ntests/regressiontests/file_uploads/tests.py\ntests/regressiontests/generic_inline_admin/tests.py','Fixed #8138 -- Changed django.test.TestCase to rollback tests (when the database supports it) instead of flushing and reloading the database.   This can substantially reduce the time it takes to run large test suites.\nThis change may be slightly backwards incompatible, if existing tests need to test transactional behavior, or if they rely on invalid assumptions or a specific test case ordering.  For the first case, django.test.TransactionTestCase should be used.  TransactionTestCase is also a quick fix to get around test case errors revealed by the new rollback approach, but a better long-term fix is to correct the test case.  See the testing doc for full details.\nMany thanks to:\n* Marc Remolt for the initial proposal and implementation.\n* Luke Plant for initial testing and improving the implementation.\n* Ramiro Morales for feedback and help with tracking down a mysterious PostgreSQL issue.\n* Eric Holscher for feedback regarding the effect of the change on the Ellington testsuite.\n* Russell Keith-Magee for guidance and feedback from beginning to end.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','kmtracey'),(6511,'9757','2009-01-16 08:59:02',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/template/__init__.py','Fixed #10014 -- Don\'t crash when using debug template tag inside a block node tag.\nReturning non-ASCII characters from TextNode.__repr__ was causing\nproblems in the BlockNode.__repr__ method (and probably in other places\nwe don\'t know about yet). We now forcibly convert to ascii and replace any\nunconvertible characters, rather than returning some moderately\ncorrupted data in the non-ASCII case.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','mtredinnick'),(6512,'9759','2009-01-16 10:59:43',0,0,3,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/query.py\ndocs/ref/models/querysets.txt\ntests/regressiontests/queries/models.py','Fixed #9997 -- Fixed use of ValuesQuerySets as rvalues in filters.\nPrevious behaviour was pretty stupid. Let\'s never speak of it again. New\nbehaviour both works and is documented.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','mtredinnick'),(6513,'9760','2009-01-16 15:32:31',4,0,4,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/admin/options.py\ndocs/ref/contrib/admin.txt\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/fixtures/admin-widgets-users.xml\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/models.py\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/tests.py\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/urls.py\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/widgetadmin.py\ntests/urls.py','Cleaned up and refactored `ModelAdmin.formfield_for_dbfield`:\n  * The new method uses an admin configuration option (`formfield_overrides`); this makes custom admin widgets especially easy.\n  * Refactored what was left of `formfield_for_dbfield` into a handful of smaller methods so that it\'s easier to hook in and return custom fields where needed.\n  * These `formfield_for_*` methods now pass around `request` so that you can easily modify fields based on request (as in #3987).\nFixes #8306, #3987, #9148.\nThanks to James Bennet for the original patch; Alex Gaynor and Brian Rosner also contributed.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','jacob'),(6514,'9761','2009-01-16 16:51:01',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/oracle/base.py','Fixed #6767: corrected a 2.3 compatibility issue in [9750]. Thanks to tlow.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','ikelly'),(6515,'9763','2009-01-16 20:05:39',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/gis/admin/options.py','Fixed geographic admin to be compatible with `ModelAdmin.formfield_for_dbfield` changes in r9760.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','jbronn'),(6516,'9764','2009-01-16 21:18:21',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'tests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/models.py\ntests/regressiontests/admin_widgets/tests.py','Changed \"date\" column to \"start_date\"--Oracle won\'t name columns with reserved keywords.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','mboersma'),(6517,'9765','2009-01-16 21:31:58',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'tests/regressiontests/forms/models.py','Fixed #10041: use a tempdir for files in the forms test. Thanks, Marty Alchin.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','jacob'),(6518,'9766','2009-01-16 21:48:37',0,0,3,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/core/files/base.py\ndjango/db/models/fields/files.py\ntests/modeltests/files/models.py','Fixed #10044: You can now assign directly to file fields (`instance.filefield = somefile`). Thanks, Marty Alchin.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','jacob'),(6519,'9767','2009-01-16 22:23:58',1,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/oracle/base.py\ntests/regressiontests/backends/tests.py','Fixed #5543: callproc() and friends now work with Oracle and our FormatStylePlaceholderCursor.',3,'2009-05-16 00:46:58','2009-05-16 00:46:58','mboersma'),(6520,'9769','2009-01-17 22:04:40',0,0,1,0,N