1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/oracle/base.py','Added savepoint support to the Oracle backend, necessary per the thread at http://groups.google.com/group/django-developers/browse_thread/thread/c87cf2d97478c068/',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6677,'10024','2009-03-10 22:48:42',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'tests/regressiontests/model_regress/models.py','Refs #10443: Added Oracle to the #10443 regression test exemption, since we don\'t yet support it.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6678,'10026','2009-03-11 03:39:34',0,0,12,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/__init__.py\ndjango/db/backends/__init__.py\ndjango/db/backends/dummy/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/mysql/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/mysql/client.py\ndjango/db/backends/oracle/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/oracle/client.py\ndjango/db/backends/postgresql/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/postgresql/client.py\ndjango/db/backends/postgresql_psycopg2/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/sqlite3/base.py\ndjango/db/backends/sqlite3/client.py','Fixed #10459 -- Refactored the internals of database connection objects so that connections know their own settings and pass around settings as dictionaries instead of passing around the Django settings module itself. This will make it easier for multiple database support. Thanks to Alex Gaynor for the initial patch.\nThis is backwards-compatible but will likely break third-party database backends. Specific API changes are:\n* BaseDatabaseWrapper.__init__() now takes a settings_dict instead of a settings module. It\'s called settings_dict to disambiguate, and for easy grepability. This should be a dictionary containing DATABASE_NAME, etc.\n* BaseDatabaseWrapper has a settings_dict attribute instead of an options attribute. BaseDatabaseWrapper.options is now BaseDatabaseWrapper[\'DATABASE_OPTIONS\']\n* BaseDatabaseWrapper._cursor() no longer takes a settings argument.\n* BaseDatabaseClient.__init__() now takes a connection argument (a DatabaseWrapper instance) instead of no arguments.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','adrian'),(6679,'10027','2009-03-11 04:56:13',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/creation.py','Fixed some breakages in the test database handling from r10026.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6680,'10028','2009-03-11 05:48:26',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/gis/db/backend/postgis/creation.py\ndjango/db/backends/creation.py','Fixed the django.contrib.gis test database creation as well.\nRefs r10026 and r10027.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6681,'10029','2009-03-11 07:06:50',0,0,8,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/__init__.py\ndjango/db/backends/postgresql_psycopg2/base.py\ndjango/db/models/query.py\ndjango/db/models/sql/subqueries.py\ndjango/db/transaction.py\ndocs/ref/databases.txt\ndocs/topics/db/queries.txt\ndocs/topics/db/transactions.txt','Fixed #3460 -- Added an ability to enable true autocommit for psycopg2 backend.\nEnsure to read the documentation before blindly enabling this: requires some\ncode audits first, but might well be worth it for busy sites.\nThanks to nicferrier, iamseb and Richard Davies for help with this patch.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6682,'10030','2009-03-11 11:03:36',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/mysql/base.py','Fixed #10463 -- Corrected a problem with the MySQL backend, introduced by [10026].',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','russellm'),(6683,'10031','2009-03-11 13:27:03',0,0,6,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/core/cache/backends/base.py\ndjango/core/cache/backends/db.py\ndjango/core/cache/backends/memcached.py\ndocs/internals/contributing.txt\ndocs/topics/cache.txt\ntests/regressiontests/cache/tests.py','Fixed #6464 -- Added incr() and decr() operations on cache backends. Atomic on Memcache; implemented as a 2 stage retrieve/update on other backends. Includes refactor of the cache tests to ensure all the backends are actually tested, and a fix to the DB cache backend that was discovered as a result. Thanks to Michael Malone for the original patch.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','russellm'),(6684,'10032','2009-03-11 21:14:18',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/oracle/creation.py','Fixed some breakages in the Oracle test database handling from r10026.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6685,'10033','2009-03-12 05:30:51',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/postgresql_psycopg2/base.py','Slight refactoring of isolation setting from r10029.\nThere was a bug in the way we were reading the DATABASE_OPTIONS setting\nand a lot of essentially duplicated code. This is neater.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6686,'10034','2009-03-12 05:31:34',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/sql/subqueries.py','Return last insert ID correctly when the feature is enabled.\nThis was overlooked when merging the patch from #3460 in r10029.\nThank to Ian Kelly for noticing. Refs #10467.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6687,'10035','2009-03-12 05:32:00',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/postgresql_psycopg2/base.py','Fixed #10467 -- Fixed generated INSERT SQL for PostgreSQL 8.1 and earlier.\nI introduced a bad regression in r10029, forgetting to check that some\nsyntax was supported. For now, you can\'t use autocommit=True with 8.1\nand earlier (it\'s still available for later versions). I\'ll fix the\nbroader issue later and re-enable it for those versions, but I want to\nget the SQL regression for the default path out of the code right now.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6688,'10036','2009-03-12 07:27:47',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/core/handlers/base.py','Fixed #10470 -- Fixed a race condition in middleware initialization.\nThanks to Travis Terry and mrts.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6689,'10037','2009-03-12 07:28:22'