load_backend. Thanks to Alex Gaynor for the initial patch',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','adrian'),(6695,'10046','2009-03-13 04:45:11',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/__init__.py','Improved the error message in case of an invalid DATABASE_BACKEND to ignore \'.svn\' directories in displaying the list of valid backends',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','adrian'),(6696,'10047','2009-03-13 16:57:26',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/sql/subqueries.py','Prevented InsertQuery from appending a \'RETURNING\' clause when it\'s not actually interested in the result.  This was causing some problems for Oracle.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6697,'10048','2009-03-13 17:20:52',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/sql/query.py','Fixed a case where column aliases weren\'t being quoted properly.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6698,'10049','2009-03-13 19:57:00',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/oracle/query.py\ntests/regressiontests/datatypes/models.py','Fixed #10238: coerce TextField values to unicode in the oracle backend.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6699,'10051','2009-03-13 21:04:48',0,0,3,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/core/cache/backends/db.py\ndjango/db/backends/__init__.py\ndjango/db/backends/oracle/base.py','Fixed #10488: fixed DB cache backend test failures in Oracle.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','ikelly'),(6700,'10053','2009-03-14 04:32:52',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/sql/query.py\ntests/regressiontests/aggregation_regress/models.py','Fixed #10425 -- Corrected the interaction of .count() with .annotate() when .values() is also involved. Thanks to kmassey for the report.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','russellm'),(6701,'10054','2009-03-14 05:18:02',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/bin/daily_cleanup.py','Fixed #10102 -- Set svn:executable on daily_cleanup script. Thanks to John Scott for the report',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','russellm'),(6702,'10055','2009-03-14 22:51:05',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/cache.txt','Made a bunch of edits to docs/topics/cache.txt, mostly based on stuff from the Django Book',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','adrian'),(6703,'10056','2009-03-15 03:41:33',2,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/base.py\ndjango/db/models/manager.py\ntests/regressiontests/custom_managers_regress/__init__.py\ntests/regressiontests/custom_managers_regress/models.py','Use plain model.Manager, or suitable proxy, for model saving.\nWe can\'t use the default manager in Model.save_base(), since we need to\nretrieve existing objects which might be filtered out by that manager. We now\nalways use a plain Manager instance at that point (or something that can\nreplace it, such as a GeoManager), making all existing rows in the\ndatabase visible to the saving code.\nThe logic for detecting a \"suitable replacement\" plain base is the same as for\nrelated fields: if the use_for_related_fields is set on the manager subclass,\nwe can use it. The general requirement here is that we want a base class that\nreturns the appropriate QuerySet subclass, but does not restrict the rows\nreturned.\nFixed #8990, #9527.\nRefs #2698 (which is not fixed by this change, but it\'s the first part of a\nlarger change to fix that bug.)',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6704,'10057','2009-03-15 03:42:08',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/db/managers.txt','Clarified and expanded documentation for Manager.use_for_related_fields.\nThis is for Manager subclasses that are default managers, but only\nsometimes.  The general rule is: \"don\'t use it.\" If you really need it,\nread the instructions.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6705,'10058','2009-03-15 03:42:31',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/db/managers.txt','Documented patterns for adding extra managers to model subclasses.\nThis seems to have been a source of confusion, so now we have some explicit\nexamples. Fixed #9676.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','mtredinnick'),(6706,'10062','2009-03-15 05:05:26',0,0,3,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/forms/models.py\ndocs/topics/forms/modelforms.txt\ntests/modeltests/model_forms/models.py','Fixed #8164 -- Fields on a ModelForm are now ordered in the order specified in the fields attribute of the ModelForm\'s Meta class. Thanks to Alex Gaynor for the patch.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','russellm'),(6707,'10063','2009-03-15 05:54:28',3,0,8,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/auth/backends.py\ndjango/contrib/auth/middleware.py\ndjango/contrib/auth/tests/__init__.py\ndjango/contrib/auth/tests/remote_user.py\ndocs/howto/auth-remote-user.txt\ndocs/howto/index.txt\ndocs/ref/authbackends.txt\ndocs/ref/index.txt\ndocs/ref/request-response.txt\ndocs/topics/auth.txt\ndocs/topics/index.txt','Fixed #689 -- Added a middleware and authentication backend to contrib.auth for supporting external authentication solutions.  Thanks to all who contributed to this patch, including Ian Holsman, garthk, Koen Biermans, Marc Fargas, ekarulf, and Ramiro Morales.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:03','2009-05-16 00:47:03','gwilson'),(6708,'10064','2009-03-15 11:21:41',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/topics/forms/modelforms.txt','Fixed #10507 -- Corrected formatting problem in ModelForm docs. Thanks to Paul Menzel for the report.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','russellm'),(6709,'10065','2009-03-16 00:34:58',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/postgresql_psycopg2/base.py','More fixing of PostgreSQL < 8.2 problems with the psycopg2 backend.\nAffects the postgresql_psycopg2 backend only. We now don\'t use the\n\"RETURNING\" syntax in SQL INSERT statements unless it\'s required by the\nautocommit behaviour. This fixes an edge-case that could cause crashes\nwith earlier PostgreSQL versions, but the broader problem remains to be\nfixed (which is #10509).\nFixed #1046