'2009-03-19 09:04:19',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/ref/models/options.txt\ndocs/topics/db/models.txt','Added some documentation explaining \"managed=False\" vs. \"proxy=True\".\nThese features look similar, but they\'re not identical. They can\'t be merged\ninto one (without requiring at least two Meta parameters anyway), so we\'ve made\nthem have APIs that match their natural use-cases most easily.\nAnyway, the documentation explains both the details and gives some simple to\nfollow rules.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6723,'10090','2009-03-19 09:06:04',2,0,8,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/base.py\ndjango/db/models/manager.py\ndjango/db/models/options.py\ndjango/db/models/query.py\ndjango/db/models/query_utils.py\ndjango/db/models/sql/query.py\ndocs/ref/models/querysets.txt\ntests/modeltests/defer/__init__.py\ntests/modeltests/defer/models.py\ntests/regressiontests/queries/models.py','Fixed #5420 -- Added support for delayed loading of model fields.\nIn extreme cases, some fields are expensive to load from the database\n(e.g. GIS fields requiring conversion, or large text fields). This\ncommit adds defer() and only() methods to querysets that allow the\ncaller to specify which fields should not be loaded unless they are\naccessed.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6724,'10091','2009-03-19 09:43:45',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/query.py','Typo fix for an error path in r100090.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6725,'10092','2009-03-19 22:46:28',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'tests/modeltests/defer/models.py','Added a test for defer() / only() to make sure saving continues to work.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6726,'10093','2009-03-19 22:46:49',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/ref/models/options.txt','Fixed #10546 -- Fixed a docs typo noticed by carljm.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6727,'10094','2009-03-19 23:14:20',0,0,4,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/conf/global_settings.py\ndjango/conf/project_template/settings.py\ndocs/ref/contrib/csrf.txt\ndocs/releases/1.1-alpha-1.txt','Added CSRF middleware to default settings and updated docs.\nUpdated docs to reflect the change, and the fact that using the\ntwo separate middleware is preferred to using the combined one.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','lukeplant'),(6728,'10095','2009-03-19 23:28:16',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/ref/settings.txt\ndocs/topics/http/middleware.txt','Updated all refs to default middleware in docs.\n(adding CSRF, removing XView which is no longer a default)',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','lukeplant'),(6729,'10096','2009-03-20 00:51:54',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/utils/_threading_local.py','Fixed database backend creation for Python 2.3.\nPreviously on \"things we changed in the recent past\".... the database\nconnection setup was changed. People were happy. Except for those\nrunning on Python 2.3.\nWe had completely broken Django on Python 2.3. Turns out, this is due to\na long-standing bug in the _threading_local module that interacts with\nobject creation in 2.3.\nInterestingly, although the bug remains in Python 2.4 and 2.5, they\ndon\'t trip over it for reasons I don\'t entirely understand at the\nmoment.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6730,'10097','2009-03-20 00:56:56',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/utils/_threading_local.py','Whoops. I left some debugging printing in r10096. Nothing to see here.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6731,'10098','2009-03-20 00:58:35',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/utils/_threading_local.py','More typo fixing. :-(\nI\'m crawling into my hole now.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6732,'10099','2009-03-20 01:37:11',0,0,2,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/base.py\ntests/regressiontests/queries/models.py','Fixed #10547 -- Worked around some odd behaviour in Python 2.3 and 2.4.\nCalling the super() version of __reduce__ in Model.__reduce__ led to infinite\nloops in Python prior to 2.5. We don\'t do that any longer.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6733,'10100','2009-03-20 01:37:34',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/test/testcases.py','Python 2.3 fix: assertTrue *still* doesn\'t exist in Python 2.3\nThe tests and testing framework should use failUnless() instead.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6734,'10101','2009-03-20 01:43:35',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/core/servers/fastcgi.py','Fixed #10556 -- Fixed a problem in the fastcgi server after r10088.\nThanks, Boo.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6735,'10102','2009-03-20 02:10:47',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/gis/maps/google/gmap.py','Fixed #10480 -- made `icons` a property to add more flexibility.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','jbronn'),(6736,'10103','2009-03-20 02:50:48',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/contrib/gis/tests/__init__.py','GeoDjango test suite now takes advantage of `importlib` added in r10088.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','jbronn'),(6737,'10104','2009-03-20 03:57:12',0,0,3,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/models/base.py\ndjango/db/models/fields/related.py\ntests/regressiontests/custom_managers_regress/models.py','Fixed #2698 -- Fixed deleting in the presence of custom managers.\nA custom manager on a related object that filtered away objects would prevent\nthose objects being deleted via the relation. This is now fixed.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','mtredinnick'),(6738,'10105','2009-03-20 03:57:21',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'django/db/backends/sqlite3/base.py','Fixed #9628 -- Use `pysqlite2` for database backend, if installed.',3,'2009-05-16 00:47:04','2009-05-16 00:47:04','jbronn'),(6739,'10107','2009-03-20 23:15:27',0,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'docs/ref/models/options.txt','Added some further clarification to 